# MacArthur HAT – CAN interface initialisation for NMEA2000
#
# When the MCP2515 socketcan interface appears, configure it for NMEA2000
# (250 kbit/s) and bring it up.  restart-ms causes automatic bus-off
# recovery after 100 ms, which is standard practice for NMEA2000 nodes.
#
# This rule fires for can0 only.  If a second CAN interface exists on the
# system it will appear as can1 and must be configured separately.

ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="net", KERNEL=="can0", \
    RUN+="/bin/ip link set can0 up type can bitrate 250000 restart-ms 100"
